reviewText: ALL RIEU DVD'S ARE ABOUT THE SAME  MUSIC BUT SOMEHOW HE MAKES EACH ONE SEEM NEW.THE PIANO MUSIC, "BALLAD TO ADALINE," IS REALLY NICE.THE BRAZILIAN  ARE NICELY DRESSED AND A HANDSOME PEOPLE WITH A LOT OF ENTHUSIASM.I LOVED THIS DVD.
summary: BRAZIL LOVES RIEU, SO DO I
Title: Live in Brazil

reviewText: Andre and his orchestra continue to shine on the world stage on their global tours.  This Live in Brazil matches their very best performances and is a welcome addition to your Andre Rieu collection.  Highly recommend this.
Title: Live in Brazil

reviewText: Like any DVD from Andre Rieu they are all super, the presentation, the music the video of the orchestra, the solist, ou name it, there simply is'nt any other music director that get that kind of entusiasme from his members!I'l recomend buying for any one who loves music.
Title: Live in Brazil

reviewText: The reaction by the people of Brazil was somethingthat added to the DVD.  They really enjoyed his presentation.I have all of his DVD and this one rates in the top 5.
summary: Always worth viewing any of his DVDs

reviewText: Great frequency respose and fine programing. I loved it very much.  Also great selection of artists.  I loved it. Great audience response also/

reviewText: How can this man bring so much joy to so many people? I have 20 of his DVDs  and plan to buy more.

reviewText: This was a great dvd and blu ray kinda short compared to others he has done,but I really want to see Andre release his Concert in Australia in 2010 with the fabulous Seekers..Come on Andre you give the public what they want and they want this concert......
summary: When Are we getting Andres Concert with The Seekers from Australia?
